  "A 3D engine uses back-face culling. A triangle has normal n = <0, 0, -1> and the camera looks in direction d = <0, 0, -1>. Should this triangle be rendered?": "",
  "No, because the normal is negative": "",
  "Yes, because n . d = 1 > 0 (facing toward camera)": "",
  "Cannot determine without more information": "",
  "No, because n . d = 1 > 0 (facing away from camera)": "",
  "n . d = 0+0+(-1)(-1) = 1 > 0. When the normal and viewing direction are in the same general direction (positive dot product), the surface faces the camera and should be rendered. (Note: conventions vary; some use the vector from surface to camera.)": "",
  "A physics engine computes the collision normal between two circles centered at C1 = (2, 3) and C2 = (6, 6). What is the unit collision normal pointing from C1 to C2?": "",
  "<3/5, 4/5>": "",
  "<4, 3>": "",
